olive oil
1 white turnip
1 carrot
1 beetroot
½ Onion
1 packet flaked almonds
2 packet chicken breast
1 sachet Garlic & Herb Seasoning
1 tsp honey
1 packet Baby Leaves
drizzle vinegar (balsamic or white wine)
1 packet Chargrilled Capsicum Relish
1 packet Garlic Dip

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced.
• Cut white turnip and carrot into bite-sized chunks. Cut beetroot into small chunks. Slice onion into wedges.

• Place veggies on a lined oven tray. Drizzle with olive oil, season with salt and toss to coat. Roast until tender, 20-25 minutes.
• When the veggies have 5 minutes remaining, add flaked almonds to the tray and allow to toast.

TIP: If your oven tray is crowded, divide between two trays.

• Meanwhile, place your hand flat on top of chicken breast and slice through horizontally to make two thin steaks.
• In a medium bowl, combine chicken, garlic & herb seasoning and a drizzle of olive oil.

• Return the frying pan to medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Cook chicken until cooked through, 3-5 minutes each side (cook in batches if your pan is getting crowded).
• Remove pan from heat, then add the honey, turning chicken to coat.

TIP: The chicken is cooked through when it's no longer pink inside.

• When the veggies are done, remove tray from oven, add baby spinach leaves and a drizzle of vinegar and toss to combine. Season to taste.
• In a small bowl, combine chargrilled capsicum relish and tahini.

• Slice the chicken.
• Divide rainbow veggie toss between bowls.
• Top with herby chicken and chargrilled capsicum tahini sauce. Enjoy!

Little cooks: Add the finishing touch by drizzling over the tahini sauce!